onite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 11:24:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.iinet.net.au/~zaptrudr/Eatbigcookie.jpg HEIGHT = 113 WIDTH = 150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> Because tablets are kinda rare and hard to get a hold of in these parts of the world... (have to order them in) I haven't actually seen a tablet in use... much less used one myself... so I have a few questions... the answers to which may decide whether i spend 200$ or 50$ or nothing at all on a new tablet.<br>
<br>
Whats the difference between a nameless brand tablet and a wacom? I'm only planning to buy at most a graphire... but even that is a little pricey. But if theres not much of a tangible difference apart from packaged software... I think I'll happily opt for a cheaper tablet.<br>
<br>
does 512 additional pressure levels make much of a difference (for those that can compare an intuos to a graphire)... similarly does an additional 256 pressure levels make that much of a difference?<br>
<br>
Also... when actually using the tablet... does the pen need contact with tablet? whats actually picking up the lines? the pen or tablet? could I use a normal pencil on a piece of paper thats stuck to the tablet?<br>
<br>
Are there pens that have a marking device? so you can actually put a piece of paper on the tablet and draw on the paper and screen simultaneously?<br>
<br>
Is it a button pressing thing? (like the mouse) if so... wheres the button located?<br>
<br>
finally.. the 4*5 area of the graphire.. does that represent the area of the screen? or is it the area of the image? (so could i zoom in and then start drawing with a magnified view... or zoom out and draw small.... then zoom in create new layers and clean up from there)<br>
<br>
thanks to anyone and everyone that helps me with these questions :) <p>Welcome to Zap's Palace and Fine Emporium,<BR>Featuring his harem of 1001 beautiful women and exotic goods.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukymhakan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kymhakan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 12:11:54 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.xenogears.f2s.com/Pics/may.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> Well for one thing, I got an intuos. I just got it today, so I'm not too good at using it yet.<br>
<br>
I dont know about the pressure thing because I never used a graphire before.<br>
<br>
U cannot use a normal pencil, but you can place a sheet of paper under the clear screen so you can trace.<br>
<br>
From what I see, the 4x5 area respresents the entire screen. The mouse button is the one on the pen itself.<br>
<br>
Hope some one else answers those other ones. I have a question tho, is there any exercises I can do to get used to the wacom. I tried colouring, but my hand is shaky and the lines do not come out clean. Is there a way to reduce the settings of the pressure so that it's not so huge? <br>
<br>
For shading in areas, do you make a selection, then shade, or do you just make a new layer and shade? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uplatinumdraco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Platinum Draco</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 12:26:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
1. quality<br>
<br>
2. if you are CGing as a hobby, a graphire is all you need,<br>
the pressure sensitivty is useful when inking, airbrushing, and painting, just have fun with it.<br>
<br>
3. the tablet is a radio proximity thingy, if you pulled the stylus apart, (DON'T) you would see a magnet and circut board wrapped in copper wire. the harder you press, the pen registers, sends it to the comp, and there is your line.<br>
<br>
the tablet can funtion as a mouse, but not very well, to move the cursor, you hold the stylus above the boxy area and move it, to click, just tap the pen tip against the surface of said box. to drag, simply press down on target, and pull away with stylus in contact.<br>
<br>
and there is this plastic filmy thing that you can stick stuff under for tracing or fun, but it isn't meant for that.<br>
<br>
4. i have no idea what a marking device is, you have to have the tablet and the stylus to use either one, no sseparate media required.<br>
<br>
the boxy area is the screen, it takes some getting used to, but it'l come. <p>"And we didn't use the metal giant dragon thing <i>why?</i>"
<br> ~ Serra
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukymhakan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kymhakan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 12:32:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.xenogears.f2s.com/Pics/may.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> When I draw, the lines sometimes become either jagged, or they're chunky in a way. Should I lower the speed, or just draw slower? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uzaptrudr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zaptrudr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 12:57:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.iinet.net.au/~zaptrudr/Eatbigcookie.jpg HEIGHT = 113 WIDTH = 150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> Oh yah... also... for the intuos people... does the directional pen thingy (where it can sense the angle you're holding the stylus at) make much of a difference?<br>
<br>
 <p>Welcome to Zap's Palace and Fine Emporium,<BR>Featuring his harem of 1001 beautiful women and exotic goods.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspiderman2099.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spider Man 2099</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 1:06:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.samruby.com/Heroes/Spiderman2099/2099Spiderman.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> I've never used a graphire so I can't make any comparisons but the tilt, angle, pressure are all well worth it, in my opinion.  Don't forget that with the Intuos you can buy different types of pens.  I dunno about the graphire but the intuos pen doesn't have to touch the pad to move the cursor around.  There's a button on the front of the pen for your index finger that you can use like a mouse.  If you push the top of the button it's like left clicking and the bottom of it it's like right clicking.  I got my tablet right in the nick of time because my scanner broke like a week later.  Instead of scanning my drawings I can trace them now.  It's very difficult at fist because the 4x5 dimensions but it can be done.  Also I don't have to use paper and pencil if I don't want.  I can just draw it direcly on the computer.  The surface to write on is very smooth and slick.  If it feels too awkward at first lay a sheet of paper over the surface and use that.  It may hinder pressure sensitivity though, not sure.<br>
<br>
I would definitely hold out a little longer and get the Intuos. <p>Spider-Man

<BR><BR>Use the bumper, that's what it's for!     <BR>- Gen. Arkady Gregorovich Ourumov</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umonkeyfu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MonkeyFu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/25/01 1:11:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Que's 'bout tablets and fandagled plastic sheets</span><hr size=1> RE: The directional thingy on an Intuous tablet.<br>
<br>
I have a 9x12 tablet and although I havent used the &quot;directional thingy&quot; yet, I figure it will be useful. When working with an airbrush you will be able to crank up the pressure and get spray effects due to the angle you hold the pen at. It might not be on your list of things you gotta have but more toys = more creativity in my book.<br>
<br>
-MonkeyFu <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=1314.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=1315.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=1318.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=1318.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1318.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1318.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm3">News and Updates<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm2">Photoshop and Art questions<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm4">General Manga Discussion<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm5">Japanese Language Help<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm23">art in progress<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm13">Black and White Art<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm14">Color Art<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm19">Member's Lounge<option value="po